column2:
With qualities such as courage permanence>, beauty <saltishness>, and serenity <depth>, thou art a match for the ocean;
ityeka vyatirekoyaṃ dharmeṇaikatravartinā | pratītiviṣayaprapteirbhedasyobhayavartinaḥ ||	This is One-sided Out-matching because through a quality belonging to one party there has been brought. within the range of cognition a difference existing between both.
abhinnavelau gambhīrāvamburāśirbhavānapi | asāvañjanasaṃkāśastvaṃ tu cāmīkaradyutiḥ ||	Incapable of transgressing the bounds and unfathomable are the ocean as well as Your Honour: that one appears like black soot;

You and the ocean are both irresistible and possess great stamina Caquatic-animals and brilliance < the [sub-marine] fire> ;
sa eṣa śleṣarūpatvāt samleṣa iti gṛhyatām | sākṣepaśca sahetuśca darśyate tadapi dvayam ||	This one, because of the nature of Paronomasia, might be regarded as Paronomastic [Out matching]; the two [varieties] with Interdiction and Reason are also being shown[ ii.
sthitimānapi dhīropi ratnānāmākaropi san | tava kakṣāṃ na yātyeva malino makarālayaḥ ||	196 Although he has firm position and courage <permanence and is the store of jewels, yet that dirty ocean does not at all attain equality with you".
